Accounting and financial statements.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to improve the learner's knowledge of business English covering a range of business topics with the essential terminology in order to develop their speaking, reading, writing, and listening skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) knows and is able to use basic business terminology; 2) communicates on business issues within his/her language competences; 3) find, analyse and assess critically professional texts; 4) use sources of information including dictionaries, web-based resources and other media; 5) organize information and make presentations on business-related topics; 6) read and express their specialised knowledge orally and in writing.
